<div class="who">

      <img src="/files/pictures/picture-75311.jpg" alt="" />
  
  <a href="/users/sierra-34" title="View user profile.">Sierra 34</a></div> <!-- /.who -->

<div class="what">
    <span class="submitted">
    07/19/10 at 8:22 pm  </span>
  <span class="editcomment"> 
    </span>
  <p class="content"><p>"Of the 444 women who received a placebo gel, 60 became infected with HIV..."</p>
<p>Whoa whoa whoa whoa. These women are now infected with HIV because they were given a PLACEBO? I'm all for progress, but this sounds unethical. Are they supposed to be happy that they're martyrs for a treatment that's only 50% effective?</p>
</p>
  </div> <!-- /.what -->

</div>


